    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-03-14T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-03-14T19:00:00-05:00" n="402"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d402">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">645K.51T3/3–1451: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the United States Representative on the Trusteeship Council</hi> (<persName
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sayre</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d402fn1">Repeated for information to Paris as
                        4801 and London as 4177.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-03-14T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 14, 1951—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>783. For Sayre. Urtel 1261. <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> considers
                    undesirable make any representation to Fr and Brit re Ewe problem at present
                    time. Your statement in <gloss target="#t_TC1">TC</gloss> and text of <gloss
                        target="#t_TC1">TC</gloss> Ees make amply clear urgency of submission by
                    Administering Authorities acceptable substantive recommendations next <gloss
                        target="#t_TC1">TC</gloss>. It is <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> view
                    that Fr and Brit require time to consider what steps they may take next.
                    Meanwhile <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> will be re-examining Ewe
                    question with view to determining most useful role US can play to assist in
                    achievement of practicable solution prior to next <gloss target="#t_GA1"
                        >GA</gloss>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Webb</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
